In a large pot with boiling salted water cook rotini pasta until al dente. Rinse with cool water. In a large bowl combine cooked and drained rotini pasta, thawed sugar snap peas, thinly sliced carrots, and red onion. In small bowl combine oil, sugar, and Oriental noodle flavor packet; blend well. Pour sauce over large bowl of pasta and vegetables. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour to blend flavors. Just before serving break Oriental ramen noodles into small pieces and toss into salad. Serve chilled.